SUMMARY:Deadline: Padimai: OOPS Onchain Artist Residency 2026
DESCRIPTION:OOPS (Origin Of Primary Source) is the first edition of Padimai
  Art and Tech Studio's Onchain Artist Residency\, a three-month remote res
 idency inviting art practitioners to critically and creatively engage with
  NFTs as artistic registers and as systems of knowledge\, documentation\, 
 and access. Five practitioners are selected. SUPPORT: SGD 15\,000 honorari
 um per artist\, plus SGD 5\,000 per artist for documentation. The residenc
 y is remote\, with community engagement designed through online meetings\;
  at the end\, participants deliver three NFTs developed during the residen
 cy to Padimai. ELIGIBILITY: individual creative practitioners working at t
 he intersection of art\, technology\, and blockchain\; open internationall
 y. RESIDENCY: 20 September to 20 December 2026. DEADLINE: 15 August 2026. 
 Apply via the residency page.\n\nOrganisation: Padimai Art and Tech Studio
 \nLocation: Remote residency (Padimai is based in Singapore)\; open intern
 ationally.\nAward: SGD 15\,000 honorarium per artist plus an additional SG
 D 5\,000 per artist for documentation (audio\, video\, photography). Five 
 practitioners selected. No application fee.\nDuration: 3 months (20 Septem
 ber to 20 December 2026)\n\nMore: https://padimai.net/onchain-artist-resid
 ency/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://padimai.net/onchain-artist-residency/?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote residency (Padimai is based in Singapore)\; open internatio
 nally.
END:VEVENT
